"12 ounce bottle into tulip glass, bottled on 6/3/2014. Pours lightly hazy/cloudy bright gold color with a 1 finger dense and rocky white head with good retention, that reduces to a small cap that lingers. Nice soapy lacing clings on the glass, with a fair amount of streaming carbonation. Aromas of lemon zest, tangerine, pear, melon, orange peel, light banana, coriander, clove, pepper, bread, herbal, floral, grass, light bubblegum, and yeast earthiness. Very nice aromas with good balance and complexity of fruity/spicy yeast, coriander, and citrus hop notes; with good strength. Taste of big lemon zest, tangerine, pear, melon, orange peel, light banana, coriander, clove, pepper, bread, herbal, floral, grass, light bubblegum, and yeast earthiness. Fair amount of yeast spiciness/light hop bitterness on the finish; with lingering notes of lemon zest, tangerine, pear, melon, light banana, coriander, clove, pepper, bread, herbal, grass, and yeast earthiness on the finish for a good bit. Very nice complexity of fruity/spicy yeast, coriander, and citrus hop flavors; with a great malt/yeast/hop balance and zero cloying flavors after the finish. Medium carbonation and body; with a very smooth, crisp, and slightly sticky mouthfeel that is great. Alcohol is well hidden with no warming present after the finish. Overall this is a damn nice hoppy Belgian pale ale. All around good complexity and balance of fruity/spicy yeast, coriander, and citrus hop flavors; and very smooth and crisp to drink. A very enjoyable offering."
"Overall it is an outstanding brew, but that's just boring! I expected more. I guess blind faith of Beer Camp is a thing of the past."
