"12 ounce bottle, part of the Beer Camp Across America 12-pack. Served in a tulip, the beer pours a slightly hazy golden/orange color with about a half inch white head that stuck around a little while. There's also a good amount of lacing. Aroma is nice but light, the brew smells like pine and citrusy (grapefruit) hops and some coriander. The taste is similar to the aroma, but with the addition of some bready/grainy malt and peppery spice. Luckily the flavors aren't subtle like the aroma is. Mouthfeel/body is light/medium, it's a bit creamy and smooth with a good amount of carbonation. I liked this brew, worth a try if you've never had it before."
