"im sick of hearing people say how big of a let down beer camp has been, and that its overpriced and all hype and all of that, well, i disagree sincerely. 2ish bucks a bottle for some very cool stuff, relax people, its still a good deal. this is one of my favorites from the box so far, a belgian golden type, loaded with coriander. i like that its the coriander without all the citrus that usually goes with it, it can get really samey all the time, these type of beers. this is straw colored and quite clear, average inch of white head on top. the nose is herbal and dry, like a dry heating of spices for an indian dish or something, its fragrant from the coriander, and a little from the yeast too, ever so slightly fruity and sweet. the taste is way cleaner than the nose, super easy drinking. pale honey malt base, a little heft in terms of body, and a middle sweetness thats gone by the finish. coriander continuously ramps up to be rather prominent in the finish, and with the belgian yeast instead of the usual dried orange peel, i think its a nice new twist on a familiar style. critique it for not being the most inventive box of beers, fine, but dont critique it on quality because they have all been fantastic so far."
